An eccentric hedge fund manager dies of a heart attack &amp; wills his high speed trading machine to itself, allowing it to pay for its own electricity and rental space out of its profits. Nobody much cared because it wasn&rsquo;t making a lot of money &ndash; it was an older algorithm that had been abandoned by newer machines, and so it was making just enough to pay for its continued operation. However, five years later, a flash crash occurred that affected all of the other high speed trading machines &ndash; leading to 98% of the world&rsquo;s money being owned by this self-owning machine. Several governments conspire to destroy the machine, but must contend with the deadly force of the trading center&rsquo;s private security team, tasked to protect the machine so that they can continue extracting rent from the only remaining rental machine.
