A drug is developed that has two primary effects: 1) psychic powers, and 2) a profound feeling of unity with the universe and alignment between one&rsquo;s own life path and the universe&rsquo;s master plan. This drug becomes very popular on the black market as a research chemical &ndash; after all, many people wish they had fantastic abilities, and everybody likes being assured that they&rsquo;ve made good decisions. However, because of the precise nature of the confidence induced &ndash; a confidence in the correctness of one&rsquo;s past decisions, regardless of their nature &ndash; the drug produces a perpetual state of war: among heavy users of the drug (most of whom are trying to escape past trauma) momentary impulses are enabled by the drug, executed with the help of the drug, and justified by the drug, including destructive impulses.
