Some vampires grow thick fur to protect them from the sunlight. Others move to the ocean floor -- the abyssal zone, where no light can penetrate. Still others dig tunnels deep into the earth and live in writhing piles in the central dens. Stakes merely pin them down; they cannot die, but being trapped in sensory isolation for centuries is worse. In sunlight, they burn but are not consumed. They cannot sleep. Every moment is defined by an aching hunger that does not dissipate with acclimatization.
